Filter data based on availability and forecast date

Source: R/preprocess.R
filter_by_availability.Rd

Filter data based on availability and forecast date

filter_by_availability(
  obs,
  date = max(obs$date),
  seq_date = date,
  case_date = date
)

Arguments

obs

A data frame with the following variables: date, cases, seq_voc, and seq_total, cases_available, and seq_available. seq_available and case_available must be uniquely define data rows but other rows can be duplicated based on data availability.
date

Date at which to filter. Defaults to the maximum date in obs.
seq_date

Date from which to use available sequence data. Defaults to the forecast date.
case_date

Date from which to use available case data. Defaults to the forecast date.

Examples

latest_dt <- latest_obs(germany_covid19_delta_obs)
dt <- rbind(
  update_obs_availability(latest_dt, seq_lag = 3),
  update_obs_availability(latest_dt, seq_lag = 1)
)
# filter out duplicates and up to the present date
filter_by_availability(dt)
